#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:2
msgid "XBZRLE (Xor Based Zero Run Length Encoding)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:4
msgid ""
"Using XBZRLE (Xor Based Zero Run Length Encoding) allows for the reduction "
"of VM downtime and the total live-migration time of Virtual machines. It is "
"particularly useful for virtual machines running memory write intensive "
"workloads that are typical of large enterprise applications such as SAP ERP "
"Systems, and generally speaking for any application that uses a sparse "
"memory update pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:11
msgid ""
"Instead of sending the changed guest memory page this solution will send a "
"compressed version of the updates, thus reducing the amount of data sent "
"during live migration. In order to be able to calculate the update, the "
"previous memory pages need to be stored on the source. Those pages are "
"stored in a dedicated cache (hash table) and are accessed by their address. "
"The larger the cache size the better the chances are that the page has "
"already been stored in the cache. A small cache size will result in high "
"cache miss rate. Cache size can be changed before and during migration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:23
msgid "Format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:25
msgid ""
"The compression format performs a XOR between the previous and current "
"content of the page, where zero represents an unchanged value. The page data "
"delta is represented by zero and non zero runs. A zero run is represented by "
"its length (in bytes). A non zero run is represented by its length (in "
"bytes) and the new data. The run length is encoded using ULEB128 (http://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/LEB128)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:32
msgid ""
"There can be more than one valid encoding, the sender may send a longer "
"encoding for the benefit of reducing computation cost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:37
msgid ""
"page = zrun nzrun\n"
"       | zrun nzrun page\n"
"\n"
"zrun = length\n"
"\n"
"nzrun = length byte...\n"
"\n"
"length = uleb128 encoded integer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:46
msgid ""
"On the sender side XBZRLE is used as a compact delta encoding of page "
"updates, retrieving the old page content from the cache (default size of "
"64MB). The receiving side uses the existing page's content and XBZRLE to "
"decode the new page's content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:51
msgid ""
"This work was originally based on research results published VEE 2011: "
"Evaluation of Delta Compression Techniques for Efficient Live Migration of "
"Large Virtual Machines by Benoit, Svard, Tordsson and Elmroth. Additionally "
"the delta encoder XBRLE was improved further using the XBZRLE instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:57
msgid ""
"XBZRLE has a sustained bandwidth of 2-2.5 GB/s for typical workloads making "
"it ideal for in-line, real-time encoding such as is needed for live-"
"migration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:60
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:62
msgid "old buffer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:64
msgid ""
"1001 zeros\n"
"05 06 07 08 09 0a 0b 0c 0d 0e 0f 10 11 12 13 68 00 00 6b 00 6d\n"
"3074 zeros"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:70
msgid "new buffer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:72
msgid ""
"1001 zeros\n"
"01 02 03 04 05 06 07 08 09 0a 0b 0c 0d 0e 0f 68 00 00 67 00 69\n"
"3074 zeros"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:78
msgid "encoded buffer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:80
msgid ""
"encoded length 24\n"
"e9 07 0f 01 02 03 04 05 06 07 08 09 0a 0b 0c 0d 0e 0f 03 01 67 01 01 69"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:86
msgid "Cache update strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:88
msgid ""
"Keeping the hot pages in the cache is effective for decreasing cache misses. "
"XBZRLE uses a counter as the age of each page. The counter will increase "
"after each ram dirty bitmap sync. When a cache conflict is detected, XBZRLE "
"will only evict pages in the cache that are older than a threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:95
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:97
msgid "Verify the destination QEMU version is able to decode the new format::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:99
msgid ""
"(qemu) info migrate_capabilities\n"
"xbzrle: off\n"
"..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:103
msgid "Activate xbzrle on both source and destination::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:105
msgid "(qemu) migrate_set_capability xbzrle on"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:107
msgid ""
"Set the XBZRLE cache size - the cache size is in MBytes and should be a "
"power of 2. The cache default value is 64 MBytes (on source only)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:110
msgid "(qemu) migrate_set_parameter xbzrle-cache-size 256m"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:112
msgid "Start outgoing migration::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:114
msgid ""
"(qemu) migrate -d tcp:destination.host:4444\n"
"(qemu) info migrate\n"
"capabilities: xbzrle: on\n"
"Migration status: active\n"
"transferred ram: A kbytes\n"
"remaining ram: B kbytes\n"
"total ram: C kbytes\n"
"total time: D milliseconds\n"
"duplicate: E pages\n"
"normal: F pages\n"
"normal bytes: G kbytes\n"
"cache size: H bytes\n"
"xbzrle transferred: I kbytes\n"
"xbzrle pages: J pages\n"
"xbzrle cache miss: K pages\n"
"xbzrle cache miss rate: L\n"
"xbzrle encoding rate: M\n"
"xbzrle overflow: N"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:133
msgid ""
"xbzrle cache miss: the number of cache misses to date - high cache-miss rate "
"indicates that the cache size is set too low."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:136
msgid ""
"xbzrle overflow: the number of overflows in the decoding which where the "
"delta could not be compressed. This can happen if the changes in the pages "
"are too large or there are many short changes; for example, changing every "
"second byte (half a page)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:141
msgid ""
"Testing: Testing indicated that live migration with XBZRLE was completed in "
"110 seconds, whereas without it would not be able to complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:144
msgid "A simple synthetic memory r/w load generator:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/migration/xbzrle.rst:146
msgid ""
"#include <stdlib.h>\n"
"#include <stdio.h>\n"
"int main()\n"
"{\n"
"    char *buf = (char *) calloc(4096, 4096);\n"
"    while (1) {\n"
"        int i;\n"
"        for (i = 0; i < 4096 * 4; i++) {\n"
"            buf[i * 4096 / 4]++;\n"
"        }\n"
"        printf(\".\");\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
